programme.name: HSBC UK Ride Social
programme.description: Welcome to Britain’s biggest network of cyclists! Meet like-minded riders, create groups, and organise your own rides.

organizer.name: TFCC - Traffic Free Cycling Club
organizer.description:
Why is this group different to others?

This group is all about social riding, with the emphasis on being as much off road as possible, so due to the different terrains it’s not all about speed.

I usually try and create rides in line with what events are going on in the local area, such as Minet Park Festival, Denham Park Country fayre etc.

Why don’t people cycle more often?

Well speaking for myself, it’s all about the dangers of the road and having the opportunity to check out the local wildlife whilst cycling.  This makes the rides more enjoyable and more sociable. 

Where does this group cycle and distances?

All rides start from West Drayton Train Station (WDS) near the bike racks, the terrains usually involve bridleways/cycle lanes/canal tow paths.  Here are some examples

3 Parks – Langley, Black & Denham Parks approximately 20-30 Miles

Pub 2 Pub – Malt Shovel to the sister pub Coy Carp – 10 – 15 Miles

Park 2 Park – Minet and Cranford Parks 15 – 20 Miles

Big Park Route – Osterley and Richmond – 30+ Miles

Cycle London – Cycling into London for the prudential Freecycle Ride – 60 Miles

A to B – Ashford Staines to Brighton – 60+ Miles

Interested In Joining

We have a facebook group - TFCC Facebook Group  just join the group.

We advertise on the Hillingdon Council Events - Hillingdon Events

Contact ME – Hannah Dunn on 07867824809

organizer.name: Quest Adventure Bike Shop
organizer.description: Quest Adventure is a bike shop in Worthing, West Sussex. We organise free guided mountain bike rides on the South Downs twice a month, one mixed and one for women, as well as a free monthly women only road bike rides. The Mountain bike rides are at leisurely pace, group rides always are slower than solo efforts, they usually last 3 to 4 hours but that includes a cake stop and are approximately 15 miles. Road rides are approximately 30 miles so you'll need a moderate level of fitness.  Our mission, in addition to offering a range of  bikes, clothing and equipment for all types of riders, is to offer good advice, inspiration and motivation for all riders in the South East.

data.name: Tour de Queniborough- Beeby loop- short ride

programme.name: HSBC UK Ride Social
programme.description: Welcome to Britain’s biggest network of cyclists! Meet like-minded riders, create groups, and organise your own rides.

organizer.name: Tour de Queniborough Cycling Group
organizer.description:
The Tour de Queniborough (TDQ) Cycling Group, is not like other cycling clubs - it is a friendly social riding group, with the aim of getting people of all abilities out riding their bikes. Once you’ve made the effort to get your bike out of its hiding place and dust off the cobwebs, you can ride at your own level or try to improve your skills and fitness with the help of the TDQ cycling group. You will be riding with like minded people by your side where you can make new friends and share experiences – but best of all, the rides are free!

Every week we have the Saturday Social Ride & all the details are on the Tour de Queniborough cycling group FB page, these rides start at 9am.During the winter months we sometimes have on a Sunday morning ride. Once the nights get lighter and the weather is less punishing, our summer rides meet at 6.30pm on a Tuesday & Thursday evenings (normally during British Summer Time). We always start and finish our rides at Queniborough Village Hall, and all our rides are listed on the LetsRide website.

Our group is open to to any ability including beginners, all you need is a roadworthy bike. Its always a good idea to bring a soft drink and a snack (or two!) with you on the rides.

Under 16s are welcome but must have an accompanying adult who will be responsible for them at all times during the ride.

data.meetingPoint:
Haldon Forest Park. We will loiter around the large guide map area found between the car park and the cafe/toilets area. 

Directions (lifted from their web site in a blatant act of plagiarism)

Travelling by car on the A38 turn off at the exit for Exeter Racecourse (there are no slip roads for this turning). Follow the signs for Haldon Forest Park. The Haldon Gateway car park is signposted further along the road on the left. For the Mamhead car park follow the signs for Mamhead and Starcross from the A380.

Please don't use our postcode in your Sat Nav! It will take you to the Forestry Commission Office and not the Haldon Forest Park visitor car park. Instead, carry on past the first gateway you see ('Office entrance only' is painted on the road there) and 200 metres on you will see the main entrance.

OS Grid Reference: SX884849

programme.name: HSBC UK Ride Social
programme.description: Welcome to Britain’s biggest network of cyclists! Meet like-minded riders, create groups, and organise your own rides.

organizer.name: Hadleigh Cycling Club
organizer.description:
We are based in Hadleigh, Suffolk. Hadleigh Cycling Club started life as a Junior Club with the aim to promote cycling at grass root level and help youngsters develop their skills in the sport with the support of Babergh District Council and British Cycling. Following the success of the Junior Club, along with increasing interests/demands, we have grown and expanded to a fully independent cycling club with a range of activities, serving our community.
 
Given our roots and strong support from our local community, we are proud to be a family friendly/orientated club. The Junior Club and Social/Family Rides will always be at the heart of the club’s regular activities/programmes. We have a variety of regular rides to suit cyclists of all abilities. Many of our members also take part in many external events including some of the big annual sportives, MTB races and time trialling series.
 
We are a friendly and approachable bunch (just mad about cycling). We would love to see more people out and about on their bikes, whether it’s a gentle ride to enjoy the scenic local villages and their best cafes, or riding in a peloton through some of the lovely Suffolk countryside. Come and  join us on our rides, meet like-minded people and truly enjoy everything cycling has to offer!

programme.name: HSBC UK Ride Social
programme.description: Welcome to Britain’s biggest network of cyclists! Meet like-minded riders, create groups, and organise your own rides.

organizer.name: Tour de Queniborough Cycling Group
organizer.description:
The Tour de Queniborough (TDQ) Cycling Group, is not like other cycling clubs - it is a friendly social riding group, with the aim of getting people of all abilities out riding their bikes. Once you’ve made the effort to get your bike out of its hiding place and dust off the cobwebs, you can ride at your own level or try to improve your skills and fitness with the help of the TDQ cycling group. You will be riding with like minded people by your side where you can make new friends and share experiences – but best of all, the rides are free!

Every week we have the Saturday Social Ride & all the details are on the Tour de Queniborough cycling group FB page, these rides start at 9am.During the winter months we sometimes have on a Sunday morning ride. Once the nights get lighter and the weather is less punishing, our summer rides meet at 6.30pm on a Tuesday & Thursday evenings (normally during British Summer Time). We always start and finish our rides at Queniborough Village Hall, and all our rides are listed on the LetsRide website.

Our group is open to to any ability including beginners, all you need is a roadworthy bike. Its always a good idea to bring a soft drink and a snack (or two!) with you on the rides.

Under 16s are welcome but must have an accompanying adult who will be responsible for them at all times during the ride.
